{"lemma":"تِجارَة","slug":"تِجارَة","root":"ت.ج.ر","root_slug":"ت-ج-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ج-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تِجارَة","root":"تجر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3782"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%90%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَجَرَ (tajara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"commerce","examples":[{"text":"رِجَالٌ لَّا تُلْهِيهِمْ تِجَارَةٌ وَلَا بَيْعٌ عَن ذِكْرِ اللَّهِ وَإِقَامِ الصَّلَاةِ وَإِيتَاءِ الزَّكَاةِ يَخَافُونَ يَوْمًا تَتَقَلَّبُ فِيهِ الْقُلُوبُ وَالْأَبْصَارُ","english":"[They are] men whom neither commerce nor sale distracts from the remembrance of God and performance of prayer and giving of alms. They fear a Day in which the hearts and eyes will turn about."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"traffic"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of تَجَرَ (tajara)."},"ipa":["/ti.d͡ʒaː.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3782","headword_ar":"تِجَارَةٌ","root":"tjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from 1; (Msb;) or quasi-inf. n.; (Mgh;) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"practice of traffic, merchandise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commerce; traffic; trade; selling and buying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trade of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAjir","text_ar":"تَاجِر"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of him who sells and buys for gain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh in ii. 15;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeking of gain by selling and buying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd ibid.) [See also 1.] ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Merchandise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is sold and bought, of goods,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commodities,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"householdfurniture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a quasi-inf. n. used in the sense of a pass. part. n. (Mgh.) [Hence the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayokumo bitijaArapi AlA=xirapi","text_ar":"عَلَيْكُمْ بِتِجَارَةِ الا=خِرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep ye to the merchandise of the life to come"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}